com.fico.streamvar.api.model

Interface ModelStep<I extends AbstractRecord,O extends AbstractRecord>

  • Type Parameters:
    I - Input record type
    O - Output record type
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    MergeableModelStep<I,O>

    public interface ModelStep<I extends AbstractRecord,O extends AbstractRecord>
    Interface for a generic step in a possibly multi-step model. Concrete implementations of this interface must include a public no-args constructor.

    • Method Summary

    • Method Detail

      • initialize

        default void initialize(com.typesafe.config.Config config)
        Perform any one-time initialization that must be done before any records are processed. For example, - loading model coefficients for variable normalization and score calculation - loading data specification for input record parsing and validation - loading lookup table resources NOTE: This is not for things that will be done by the driver, like managing connections with a data store or initializing thread-local serializers and cache.
        Parameters:
        config - the model step configuration

      • calculate

        O calculate(CalculableProfileRecords profiles,
            I record)
        Perform calculations with required profiles and AbstractRecord-type input
        Parameters:
        profiles - List of Profile objects used in ModelStep
        record - Record to be processed
        Returns:
        Record to be used in next ModelStep or ScoreResponse implementing AbstractRecord

      • getProfileKeys

        default List<ProfileKey> getProfileKeys(I record)
        Get information required by the Driver to acquire, lock and pass Profile(s) to calculate()
        Parameters:
        record - Record to be processed
        Returns:
        List of ProfileKeys required by Driver to get profile objects for calculate(). If no profiles are used, empty list should be returned.
